    "Then there isK 0 ∈ N such that for every ε > 0, K ∈ N, K ≥ K 0 M ∈ N, k 0 ∈ N we have the following.",
    "Let Q 2 ≤k 0 (adj) be the collection of all the ordered pairs (Q, Q ′) where R ∈ R ≤k 0, n ∈ {0,..., K -2}, Q = Q(R, n), Q ′ = Q(R, n + 1).",
