    "Firstly, the fact that side lengths of Q and Q ′ agree whenever (Q, Q ′) ∈ Q 2 ≤k 0 (adj) is an immediate consequence of the fact that Q and Q ′ are of the same order.By Lemma 5.19, we find K 0 such that the map ρ k 0 = refine [k 0] (σ) ∈ V for every k 0 ≥ 0 and K ≥ K 0."
